DEVIATIONS from upstream Casbin
-------------------------------
- Go module path renamed to github.com/hanzoai/authz; the product is named "Hanzo Authz".
- Source file headers add "Copyright 2026 Hanzo AI, Inc." and retain the upstream
  "Portions Copyright ... The casbin Authors" attribution.
- Adds mount.go and mount_default_adapter.go: a Mount() entry point that registers the
  engine with github.com/hanzoai/cloud (cloud.Register("authz", ...)) and serves
  /v1/authz/* (Check, AddPolicy, ListPolicies, RemovePolicy) in the unified cloud binary.
- Adds ai_api.go: Enforcer.SetAIConfig and Enforcer.Explain, producing natural-language
  explanations of enforcement decisions via an OpenAI-compatible API.
- Adds a TransactionalEnforcer (enforcer_transactional.go, transaction.go,
  transaction_buffer.go, transaction_commit.go, transaction_conflict.go): atomic policy
  operations with optimistic locking and conflict detection.
- Adds a ContextEnforcer (enforcer_context.go, enforcer_context_interface.go) that wraps
  Enforcer over persist.ContextAdapter for context.Context-aware operations.
- Adds the detector package (detector/): a Detector interface and default implementation
  that checks a RoleManager for RBAC inheritance cycles.
- Depends on the Hanzo/Lux platform stack in go.mod: github.com/hanzoai/cloud,
  github.com/zap-proto/zip, github.com/luxfi/kms, github.com/luxfi/zapdb, github.com/luxfi/zap.
- CI runs on Hanzo self-hosted runners (runs-on: hanzo-build-linux-amd64 across .github/workflows/).

